-- Bank of China's Xiao Says Banks Should Speed Overseas Expansion, FT Says
-- B y   B e n   L i v e s e y
-- 2010-10-21T21:00:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/bank-of-china-s-xiao-says-banks-should-speed-overseas-expansion-ft-says.html
Bank of China Ltd .’s Chairman Xiao
Gang has called for the country’s financial industry to
accelerate expansion overseas, an indication that China is
considering allowing banks to resume offshore mergers and
acquisitions, the Financial Times reported, citing an essay by
Xiao that was published today.  In the post-financial-crisis, “banks that have the ability
should hasten their pace in ‘going abroad’ and increase their
international competitiveness,” Xiao wrote, according to the
FT.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Livesey at 
 blivesey@bloomberg.net  